## Common Adjustment Scenarios

### Scenario 1: Overcommitted

**Trigger:** "I have too many goals and I'm making no progress on any of them"

**Root Cause:** TIME - trying to do too much

**Solution:** Cut 50% of goals, focus on top 2-3

**Action:**
1. Rank goals by importance
2. Pause bottom 50%
3. Update goal-status.yaml
4. Revisit paused goals next month

### Scenario 2: Wrong Approach

**Trigger:** "I hate going to the gym, I keep skipping workouts"

**Root Cause:** MOTIVATION - method doesn't fit preferences

**Solution:** Change approach from gym to home workouts or sports

**Action:**
1. Research home workout programs
2. Try 3 options this week
3. Pick one and commit
4. Update goal from "gym 3x/week" to "workout 3x/week (home)"

### Scenario 3: External Blocker

**Trigger:** "My work schedule changed and I no longer have evenings free"

**Root Cause:** EXTERNAL BLOCKER - schedule shift

**Solution:** Move evening goals to morning or weekends

**Action:**
1. Identify which goals were evening-based
2. Test morning alternatives this week
3. Update goal timing in schedule
4. Adjust expectations if needed

### Scenario 4: Energy Mismatch

**Trigger:** "I'm exhausted after work and can't do my course"

**Root Cause:** ENERGY - trying to learn when depleted

**Solution:** Move learning to weekend mornings when fresh

**Action:**
1. Block Saturday/Sunday mornings for course
2. Reduce frequency from 5x/week to 2x/week (weekends)
3. Accept slower progress but higher quality

