Adjustments should influence next period's goals

## Best Practices

### 1. Don't Overuse
- Not for minor setbacks
- Reserve for significant issues
- 1-2 per month max

### 2. Be Honest
- No shame in adjusting
- Rigidity leads to failure
- Flexibility leads to success

### 3. Document Why
- Track trigger, cause, solution
- Learn from patterns over time
- Review adjustments in retrospectives

### 4. Follow Through
- Actually implement the solution
- Check in 1 week later
- Iterate if needed

### 5. Question the Goal
- Sometimes the goal itself is wrong
- Be willing to abandon
- Sunk cost fallacy is real

